WQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4","01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4"]}},"additionalProperties":false}},{"name":"update","description":"Applies a set of edits to the markdown document.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","required":["doc","edits"],"properties":{"doc":{"type":"string","description":"The ID of the referenced object. Formats accepted:\n- DXN (dxn:echo:@:01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4). DXNs can be prepended with an @ symbol for compatibility with in-text references.\n- space ID, object ID tuple (spaceID:objectID)\n- Only object ID that is assumed to be in the current space (01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4)","examples":["dxn:echo:@:01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4","@dxn:echo:@:01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4","BM3FSHFOMJCHCG5QW7JTVKGYABD2GAA7G:01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4","01KG7R1ZXWFMWQ4DA1Q6TN1DG4"]},"edits":{"type":"array","items":{"type":"object","required":["oldString","newString"],"properties":{"oldString":{"type":"string","description":"The text to find in the document."},"newString":{"type":"string","description":"The text to replace it with."},"replaceAll":{"type":"boolean","description":"If true, replaces all occurrences. Defaults to false (first occurrence only)."}},"additionalProperties":false},"description":"The edits to apply to the document. Each edit finds oldString and replaces it with newString."}},"additionalProperties":false}}]},"prompt":{"content":[{"role":"system","content":"## Blueprints Definitions\n\n<blueprint>\n  You can create, read and update markdown documents.\n  When asked to edit or update documents return updates as a set of compact diff string pairs.\n  For each diff, respond with the smallest possible matching span.\n  \n  Example:\n  ```diff\n  - \"There is a tyop in this sentence.\"\n  + \"There is a typo in this sentence.\"\n  - \"This id good.\"\n  + \"This sentence is really good.\"\n  ```\n</blueprint>","options":{}},{"role":"user","content":"Create a document with a cookie recipe.","options":{}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"reasoning","text":"The user wants me to create a document with a cookie recipe. Let me create a nice markdown document with a classic cookie recipe.","options":{}},{"type":"tool-call","id":"toolu_01EtanYXQPvZAbcu8KJZu5he","name":"create","params":{"name":"Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies","content":"# Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\nA timeless recipe for soft, chewy chocolate chip cookies that are golden on the edges and gooey in the center.\n\n## Ingredients\n\n- 2 ¼ cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 tsp baking soda\n- 1 tsp salt\n- 1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened\n- ¾ cup granulated sugar\n- ¾ cup packed brown sugar\n- 2 large eggs\n- 2 tsp vanilla extract\n- 2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Preheat** your oven to 375°F (190°C). Line baking sheets with parchment paper.\n2. **Combine dry ingredients:** In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.\n3. **Cream the butter and sugars:** In a large bowl, beat the softened butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar together until light and fluffy, about 3–4 minutes.\n4. **Add eggs and vanilla:** Beat in the eggs one at a time, then mix in the vanilla extract until well combined.\n5. **Mix in dry ingredients:** Gradually add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients, mixing on low speed until just combined. Do not overmix.\n6. **Fold in chocolate chips:** Stir in the chocolate chips with a spatula or wooden spoon.\n7. **Scoop the dough:** Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheets, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\n8. **Bake:** Bake for 9–11 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown but the centers still look slightly underdone.\n9. **Cool:** Let the cookies cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n## Tips\n\n- For extra flavor, use a mix of semi-sweet and dark chocolate chips.\n- Chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking for thicker cookies.\n- Store in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 5 days.\n\n**Yield:** ~48 cookies | **Prep Time:** 15 min | **Bake Time:** 10 min\n"},"providerExecuted":false,"options":{}}],"options":{}},{"role":"tool","content":[{"type":"tool-result","id":"toolu_01EtanYXQPvZAbcu8KJZu5he","name":"create","isFailure":false,"result":{"_id":"Exit","_tag":"Success","value":{"id":"dxn:echo:BDJXMULPW5FB55UZ7KP5HLDHVTXUTHE2U:01JGFJJZ00G0WKQSJGMAKCNTHZ"}},"providerExecuted":false,"options":{}}],"options":{"anthropic":{"cacheControl":{"ttl":"5m","type":"ephemeral"}}}}]},"response":[{"type":"response-metadata","id":"msg_019uQpmJUSKBiH14HcEW3o9T","modelId":"claude-opus-4-6","timestamp":"2026-05-17T07:06:48.391Z","metadata":{}},{"type":"reasoning-start","id":"0","metadata":{}},{"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"The","metadata":{}},{"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":" document was created successfully.","metadata":{}},{"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"","metadata":{"anthropic":{"type":"thinking","signature":""}}},{"type":"reasoning-end","id":"0","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-start","id":"1","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"I've created a **Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies** recipe document for you! 🍪 ","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"It includes:\n\n- **Ingredients** – a full list with measurements for a","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" classic batch\n- **Step-by-step instructions** – from preheating the oven to cooling the cookies\n- **Tips** – for extra flavor, th","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"icker cookies, and proper storage\n\nThe recipe yields about 48 cookies. Let me know if you'd like to make","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" any changes, such as adjusting ingredients, adding variations, or tweaking the instructions!","metadata":{}},{"type":"text-end","id":"1","metadata":{}},{"type":"finish","reason":"stop","usage":{"inputTokens":2254,"outputTokens":142,"totalTokens":2396},"metadata":{"anthropic